The paper focuses on the task of Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves processing visual information using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and natural language processing using recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes an efficient and modular neural architecture for VQA, which involves training a sparsely activated CNN. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
